ZCZC OE25
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 192300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A HIGH PRESSURE 1043 WILL BE CENTRED IN THE BALTIC
SEA. A SLOW-MOV ATLANTIC LOW PRESSURE 988 WILL LIE TO THE W OF IRELAND
WITH UK WATERS IN S FLOW BETWEEN THESE FEATURES. THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY
THE ATLANTIC LOW TO THE W WILL FILL WITH SHALLOW LOW CENTRES CONNECTED TO
THIS EXP TO FORM AROUND ICELAND DURING TUESDAY BUT THEN QCKY FLN AND MOV
EWARDS EARLY WEDNESDAY. THE HIGH OVER THE BALTIC SEA WILL TRANSFER WWARDS
DURING TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY TO BE CENTRED NERN ENGLAND AROUND 1036 BY MIDDAY
THURSDAY ALLOWING HIGH PRESSURE TO DOMINATE MOST UK SEA AREAS. NO STRG WINDS
ARE EXP MONDAY EVENING. STRG WINDS ARE POSS FOR SHANNON AND ROCKALL AT TIMES
DURING TUESDAY AND THEN OVERNIGHT TUESDAY INTO WEDNESDAY FOR S E ICELAND.
NO HAZARDOUS WINDS EXP ACROSS PORTPATRICK ON THURSDAY
